    <h2 class="section-title">Extra Policies &amp; Details</h2>
    
    <div class="policies-grid">

      <details class="policy-card" data-policy="terms-of-service">
        <summary>Terms of Service</summary>
        <div class="content-inner">
          <p class="date">Last updated: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>By using Poke, or by creating and utilizing a Poke account, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. Poke is a <strong>free software</strong>, community-driven project and is provided entirely "as is" and "as available", without any warranties of any kind, whether express or implied.</p>
          <p>You agree to use Poke responsibly. You strictly may not use our service or infrastructure to conduct DDoS attacks, distribute spam, exploit system vulnerabilities, or engage in any other malicious or illegal activities that degrade the platform for others.</p>
          <p>Poke is fully committed to user freedom. Our software is licensed under the <strong>GNU General Public License version 3 (GPLv3)</strong> or any later version, guaranteeing your right to freely use, study, modify, and distribute the code.</p>
          <p>Your use of the platform and your Poke account are also subject to our <a href="/policies/code-of-conduct">Code of Conduct</a> and <a href="/policies/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. Maintaining a safe, inclusive, and privacy-respecting environment requires strict adherence to these community guidelines.</p>
          <p>We do not guarantee that the service will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free, and we offer <strong>zero liability</strong> to our users. The project maintainers, contributors, and instance operators accept no liability for any losses, data corruption, or damages that may arise from your use of Poke.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      
      <details class="policy-card" data-policy="dmca">
        <summary>DMCA Policy</summary>
        <div class="content-inner">
          <p class="date">Last updated: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>Poke operates strictly as a <strong>privacy-respecting frontend for YouTube</strong>. We do not host, store, alter, or upload any video content on our own infrastructure. Every piece of media viewed through Poke originates and streams directly from YouTube’s official servers.</p>
          <p>If you believe that your copyrighted material is being improperly displayed, please first verify if the content exists on YouTube directly. Because Poke simply proxies public data, the most effective and correct channel for resolution is submitting a claim via YouTube’s <a href="https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/2807622" target="_blank">official DMCA takedown form</a>. Once removed from YouTube, the content will instantly disappear from Poke.</p>
          <p>Our network and platform qualify as a <strong>transient intermediary</strong> under 17 U.S.C. § 512 (a), serving solely to transmit publicly accessible information without modification. Directing a DMCA takedown at Poke for video content is legally ineffective because we do not have control over the originating media files.</p>
          <p>In the unlikely event that our systems are erroneously scraping, mislinking, or caching material outside the scope of standard YouTube proxying, you can open an issue on our tracker at <a href="https://codeberg.org/ashleyirispuppy/poke/issues" target="_blank">https://codeberg.org/ashleyirispuppy/poke/issues</a>. Please provide clear documentation, including links to the Poke instance and the original source file.</p>
          <details>
            <summary>Privacy of Submitted Reports</summary> 
             <p>Any personal identifying information you share while filing a report will be used <strong>exclusively</strong> for evaluating and addressing your claim. This information will not be exposed to the public, sold, or aggregated.</p>
             <p>Because Poke operates without centralized user accounts, your submitted issue details will be processed manually by our maintainers and permanently expunged from our direct communications once the matter is fully resolved. We strongly encourage keeping submitted personal details to a necessary minimum.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-card" data-policy="content-source">
        <summary>Content Source &amp; Legal Basis</summary>
        <div class="content-inner">
          <p class="date">Last updated: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>Poke serves as a secure, <strong>privacy-focused gateway to YouTube</strong>, granting users a streamlined interface to public content. Our goal is to enable individuals to browse videos, read descriptions, and discover creators without facing invasive telemetry, user profiling, or aggressive advertising.</p>
          <p>We retrieve all necessary video streams, thumbnails, and descriptive metadata via YouTube’s public-facing endpoints utilizing community-maintained, reverse-engineered protocols. Poke <strong>does not</strong> integrate the official YouTube Data API v3 and is not bound by Google’s standard developer API Terms of Service.</p>
          <p>Under United States copyright framework, specifically <strong>17 U.S.C. § 512 (a)</strong>, our platform operates safely as a conduit that transmits unaltered material through a network. In the European Union, Poke’s functionality is safeguarded by Directive <strong>2001/29/EC</strong>, covering transient and incidental acts of reproduction integral to a technological process.</p>
          <p><strong>Poke is an entirely lawful project</strong>. We do not engage in piracy, rehosting, or the distribution of protected works. We simply provide a custom, user-centric viewing layer for data that Google has already made publicly accessible to the open web.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-card" data-policy="ai-training">
        <summary>AI Training Policy</summary>
        <div class="content-inner">
          <p class="date">Last updated: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>The Poke Project <strong>expressly forbids</strong> the mass scraping, downloading, or utilization of our frontend interfaces, data feeds, media streams, and community content for the purpose of training, fine-tuning, or populating artificial intelligence or machine learning models.</p>
          <p>Because Poke acts as a proxy, the underlying video material, metadata, and user comments are copyrighted works belonging to their respective creators. Processing this data through Poke's infrastructure to construct AI datasets constitutes unauthorized exploitation of creator rights and abuses our server resources.</p>
          <p>Any automated agents, organizations, or individuals detected aggregating Poke's output for LLM or generative AI training will face immediate network-level blocking and potential reporting. We build privacy tools for humans, not datasets for bots.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="policy-card" data-policy="coding-style">
        <summary>Coding Style Policy</summary>
        <div class="content-inner">
          <p class="date">Last updated: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>We want the Poke codebase to remain highly maintainable, welcoming to newcomers, and heavily standardized. If you plan to contribute, please adhere to these core formatting guidelines:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Indentation:</strong> Strictly use <strong>two spaces</strong>. Never use tabs.</li>
            <li><strong>Line Length:</strong> Strive to keep lines under 100 characters to ensure readability on split screens and smaller monitors.</li>
            <li><strong>Naming Conventions:</strong> Use incredibly clear and descriptive variable names. Avoid single-letter variables except in basic loops (like `i` or `j`).</li>
